<title>USA: Calif. regulators approve $3.3 bln PG&amp;E plan.</title>
<headline>Calif. regulators approve $3.3 bln PG&amp;E plan.</headline>
<dateline>SAN FRANCISCO 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>California's Public Utilities Commission on Wednesday approved a plan allowing PG&amp;E Corp's Pacific Gas &amp; Electric to recover $3.3 billion spent on the Diablo Canyon nuclear power plant.</p>
<p>The commission said the plan would allow Pacific Gas &amp; Electric to recover over a five-year period the remaining or &quot;sunk&quot; costs of building the plant.</p>
<p>The commission said the plan should help Diablo Canyon compete in the soon-to-be deregulated state electricity market.</p>
